    main view and teaches the main controller to use it when appropriate.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 7ebc3b30cec8f6bcdc3355ffeef2613ef2c139dd
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 18 01:25:59 2009 -0700

    models/main: properly handle diff expressions with whitespace
    
    We did not properly handle 'HEAD^ HEAD' because of the embedded space.
    We now properly handle this by splitting arguments before passing
    them along to git.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 2fdcc1662846c59a483b449113a33bb9f8d0028a
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 18 01:09:14 2009 -0700

    models: introduce get_diff_by_expr() and use it in the main controller
    
    We no longer rely on heuristics when deciding how to construct
    arguments intended for git diff.  The controller knows what mode
    it's in and thus never rely on heuristics.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 8a9726ef2d2ac674a82551499c7eb49f4baa9df9
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 18 00:50:22 2009 -0700

    models/main: use a more robust method to detect when not to use --cached
    
    We were incorrectly passing --cached in some instances when using
    `diff-by-expression` or `diff-mode`.  This fixes things so
    that we are more robust to free-form input.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit cae2b6e47ef290c7f39048c701e5e2772cfdaeb9
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 18 00:35:51 2009 -0700

    branch review: use $(git merge-base HEAD branch)..branch in review mode
    
    We used to use ...branchname when showing the diff for review mode.
    We now use `$(git merge-base HEAD branchname)..branchname` since it
    is more robust.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 66cd8a8ed7948a5d573bcb277a46e155dc5fe312
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 16 21:23:10 2009 -0700

    controllers/main: always use 'HEAD' when undoing changes
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit ccf1ca126c6d607a63e8e5d56567c3d5554c7352
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 16 04:16:43 2009 -0700

    classic: handle the 'history(QStringList)' signal from the RepoTreeView
    
    We now launch the configured history browser on the selected paths.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit db946108aaf8e6230373bd2273a18fabbaed7d91
