commit 6aacd26e5fae0e346aeb28e2fb6d1956ff63d94b
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 30 11:40:14 2008 -0800

    main: add support for '--git-path=<path>'
    
    Launching cola from Windows ends up with an environment where 'git.exe'
    is not in the $PATH.  The Windows installer will supply --git-path
    which solves this issue.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 8349bcdaf530b8988e873dd58f47df284c0b6aeb
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Jan 25 21:40:37 2009 -0800

    win32/cola: update to support the Windows installer
    
    The 'dirname' function did not properly handle paths with
    embedded spaces.  Also, Windows uses git-cola.pyw instead
    of the default git-cola startup script.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 906c079524c0cfb7a9c2fdef88b1b01952ff5bcd
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Jan 25 16:27:24 2009 -0800

    git-cola: add support for the win32 installation layout
    
    Windows uses a slightly modified installation layout that does
    not include the 'python2.x' directory in its site-packages path.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit e2657c59adcf51bb12d1e9566e6c3b341acaee03 (tag: v1.3.5)
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 19 19:09:46 2009 -0800

    git-difftool: update difftool documentation to include some packaging notes
    
    difftool is now available in cola.git and git.git.
    Mention this and recommend usage of the version from git.git.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit c6b12a1442b0b0e79580bbe8391bb2e51b720b96
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 19 19:07:02 2009 -0800

    difftool: change trap condition from SIGINT to INT
    
    Markus Heidelberg provided this patch against git.git's
    contrib/difftool.
    
    In 'man 1p trap' there is written:
    
       "The condition can be EXIT, 0 (equivalent to EXIT), or a signal
        specified using a symbolic name, without the SIG prefix, [...]"
    
       "Implementations may permit names with the SIG prefix or ignore case
        in signal names as an extension."
    
    So now we do it the POSIX compliant way instead of using an extension.
    
    Signed-off-by: Markus Heidelberg <markus.heidelberg@web.de>
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit fc805e5dd33dd4f9d43837981f09049d60e761f5
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Jan 18 16:52:05 2009 -0800

    git-difftool: incorporate suggestions from the git mailing list
    
    Markus Heidelberg has a number of stylistic improvements to the
    difftool documentation and comments.  This also adds usage of the
    vim "wincmd" command for positioning the cursor at startup.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit e7a80fee4304ba25c06dd1b1527c5373b2f7a914
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 30 03:34:30 2008 -0800

    windows: make clone and open work reliably on windows
    
    os.spawnv is a nasty beast in windows-land.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 44ed8ab3bf526873e19704a296fcf06687cc288f
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 30 03:32:41 2008 -0800

    win32/cola: add Python's path to $PATH
    
    This lets us easily launch python scripts.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit c5b0ecd991d7f2ab33e8e2025908e6d27aaccbcd
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Jan 17 02:49:58 2009 -0800

    cola: use the new with_stderr flag throughout cola
    
    We now grab stderr only when we really need to do so.
    Places that care about stderr but not about the return status
    no longer need to grab it into a throw-away variable.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 5d437b618beec020340a78a645e70af1fd6732d9
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Jan 17 02:48:39 2009 -0800

    git: add a with_stderr option to control whether or not we get stderr
    
    The git command module will only include stderr when the with_stderr
    option is set to True.  This separates with_extended_output and with_stderr
    so that they do not have overlapping duties.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 9a1f2a7fa64c54c293fb73605b164bd311ad85fb
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Jan 16 18:12:56 2009 -0800

    models: simplify the model worktree status routine
    
    We no longer post-process the status data to remove unmerged
    items from the modified files list -- this is done up front
    when unmerged entries are first found.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 73ecfad6264d33abdb59bf5e9e71fc885abada54
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Jan 16 21:05:13 2009 -0800

    tests: skip serialization tests when simplejson is not available
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit dc7d7b0edf21dd4c286f0903f7f4dc66076def29
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Jan 16 21:04:57 2009 -0800

    model: simplify the deserializer by using __import__()
    
    We were using the 'imp' module to for loading modules.
    Using __import__() is simpler and more robust.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 166b38543b9a6005de7a2f3b2f5647941fb19ebb
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Jan 16 18:10:32 2009 -0800

    git: change with_extended_output to only return status, output
    
    The stderr+stdout handling in the git module was broken because it
    could deadlock on older versions of Python.  All of the complication
    came from trying to handle both stderr and stdout in the same
    function.  We now pass stderr=subprocess.STDOUT to subprocess.Popen
    so that things become much simpler.  We only include stderr when
    with_extended_output=True, otherwise we ignore it.
    
    This fixes deadlocks on older Pythons and on Mac OSX.
    It also seems to speed things up a bit on Linux, which is a plus.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit d1d3b93da32c7761f6a21ab663da458ef5bf1ac4
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Jan 16 18:08:18 2009 -0800

    tests: simplify the import test by using __import__()
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 369ae9fbc35880f6e7e061c87dbd4632801996e5
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jan 15 21:51:31 2009 -0800

    inotify: add support for pyinotify 0.8.x
    
    The pyinotify API changed between 0.7.x and 0.8.x.
    The cola.inotify module now works with both 0.8.x and as 0.7.x.
    
    We do accomplish this by checking pyinotify.__version__ at runtime
    to determine which API to use.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 761ede3ce3ea3e1bc3d5c8cf1dfc66043d6f3a3c
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 30 00:34:08 2008 -0800

    git-difftool: simplify the windows exe() handling
    
    Windows doesn't need the full path to git.exe.
    We just need to exec "git.exe" instead of "git".
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 37a01c137271d001cd71b486f05be4c412331b22
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 30 00:27:21 2008 -0800

    win32: update the 'cola' script so that it passes "$@"
    
    We were losing command-line args when run through the 'cola'
    windows wrapper script.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 273be078708beac8d77dfb101b38a6a3faaa229b
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Dec 29 23:51:36 2008 -0800

    git-difftool: add portability code for Windows
    
    git-difftool now works on Windows.
    The GIT_EXTERNAL_DIFF rewrite broke Windows.
    This makes things happy again.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 789cdd388feba59a4b11c7a3b15137ec49078d11
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jan 15 11:34:06 2009 -0800

    git: fix a deadlock on python2.4
    
    Python 2.4's subprocess.Popen requires that you read from stderr before
    reading stdout.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 540bb69c6511071d436c1281fcfad7e710ed8437
